{
  "text": "In Buerger's disease (thromboangiitis obliterans), an occlusive intraluminal thrombus with a predominantly acute inflammatory infiltrate causes ischemic ulcers, claudication, paresthesia and pain at rest [CITATION_1] 16) .",
